\title{Constructing Equalizers in Type Theory}
\date{2025-02-06T23:30:23Z}
\author{stevenschaefer}

\import{sss-001L}
\def\SigTy[arg1][arg2][arg3]{#{\ixsum{\arg1 : \arg2}{\arg3}}}

\p{
  In the presence of #{\Sigma}-types, one may construct all [equalizers](sss-001L). Given types #{A} and #{B} with functions #{f, g : A \to B}, the equalizer may be constructed as
  ##{\define{\eq\Sub{\f,\g}}{\SigTy{a}{A}{\prn{\f(a) = \g(a)}}}}
}
